.Dd $Mdocdate: March 28 2009 $
.Dt DRILLPOINTS 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm drillpoints
.Nd Lengths of drill points
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Where
.Em D
is the diameter of the drill and
.Em K
is a constant, the length of a drill
point can be computed as
.Em P = D*K .
K constants for common drill point angles are listed below:
.Bd -literal -offset left
Point angle (degs)	K constant
------------------	----------
60			0.866025404
82			0.575184204
90			0.500000000
118			0.300430310
120			0.288675135
125			0.260283525
130			0.233153829
135			0.207106781
140			0.181985117
145			0.157649394
150			0.133974596
.Ed
